<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,639,194,1118]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,290,247,268]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the 
<typeStatus box="[151,192,274,295]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">type</typeStatus>
locality, Kahurnagi National Park, 
<collectingRegion box="[538,608,274,295]" country="New Zealand" name="Nelson" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Nelson</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,639,194,1118]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,280,300,321]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Broun" authorityYear="1915" box="[446,496,327,348]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socia">
<emphasis box="[446,496,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">socia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the following combination of characters: larger body, length 
<quantity box="[289,415,379,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.6 mm</quantity>
; male antennomere 7 enlarged, as long as wide; eye prominent, onethird length of temple; male hind wings reduced to small pads; shape of genitalia unique to species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,639,194,1118]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,386,486,507]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Description of Male.</emphasis>
L e n g t h 
<quantity box="[492,608,486,508]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" unit="m" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5– 2.6 m</quantity>
m. Body reddish brown, antennae, elytra, legs, and maxillary palpi paler (
<figureCitation box="[392,486,539,560]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[175,207,1148,1167]" captionTargetBox="[162,1162,196,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-275@83.[151,1171,183,1124]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 47. Sagola species in the socia species-group. Habitus, dorsal views: a) S. socia, b) S. solodovnikovi, c) S. kahurangiensis, d) S. bullerensis, e) S. canterburyensis. Aedeagi, dorsal views: f) S. socia, g) S. solodovnikovi, h) S. kahurangiensis, i) S. bullerensis, j) S. canterburyensis. k) S. socia, dorsal surface of male head. Scale bars a–e = 1 mm, f–k = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907863/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 47c</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[508,574,539,560]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Head:</emphasis>
Head round, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[409,492,566,587]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[175,207,1148,1167]" captionTargetBox="[162,1162,196,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-275@83.[151,1171,183,1124]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 47. Sagola species in the socia species-group. Habitus, dorsal views: a) S. socia, b) S. solodovnikovi, c) S. kahurangiensis, d) S. bullerensis, e) S. canterburyensis. Aedeagi, dorsal views: f) S. socia, g) S. solodovnikovi, h) S. kahurangiensis, i) S. bullerensis, j) S. canterburyensis. k) S. socia, dorsal surface of male head. Scale bars a–e = 1 mm, f–k = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907863/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 47c</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 1 approximately 1.5 times longer than wide, 2 longer than wide, 3–10 subquadrate, 7 enlarged, 4–11 bearing tubercles. Frontal sulcus deep, reaching posterior end of eye. Anterior frontal fovea oval, partially covered by frontal rostrum, posterior frontal fovea oval. Eye prominent, approximately one-third length of temple. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[430,515,752,773]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Thorax:</emphasis>
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at midpoint. Elytra rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[221,312,805,826]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[175,207,1148,1167]" captionTargetBox="[162,1162,196,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-275@83.[151,1171,183,1124]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 47. Sagola species in the socia species-group. Habitus, dorsal views: a) S. socia, b) S. solodovnikovi, c) S. kahurangiensis, d) S. bullerensis, e) S. canterburyensis. Aedeagi, dorsal views: f) S. socia, g) S. solodovnikovi, h) S. kahurangiensis, i) S. bullerensis, j) S. canterburyensis. k) S. socia, dorsal surface of male head. Scale bars a–e = 1 mm, f–k = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907863/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 47c</figureCitation>
). Hind wings reduced to small pads. Meso- and metathorax trapezoidal, longer than wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[261,369,858,879]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Tergite IV without patches of microtrichia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[314,421,885,906]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Median lobe divided vertically, major lobe narrower than minor lobe (
<figureCitation box="[158,243,938,959]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[175,207,1148,1167]" captionTargetBox="[162,1162,196,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-275@83.[151,1171,183,1124]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 47. Sagola species in the socia species-group. Habitus, dorsal views: a) S. socia, b) S. solodovnikovi, c) S. kahurangiensis, d) S. bullerensis, e) S. canterburyensis. Aedeagi, dorsal views: f) S. socia, g) S. solodovnikovi, h) S. kahurangiensis, i) S. bullerensis, j) S. canterburyensis. k) S. socia, dorsal surface of male head. Scale bars a–e = 1 mm, f–k = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907863/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 47h</figureCitation>
). Phallobase of median lobe symmetrical and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[295,386,964,985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[175,207,1148,1167]" captionTargetBox="[162,1162,196,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-275@83.[151,1171,183,1124]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 47. Sagola species in the socia species-group. Habitus, dorsal views: a) S. socia, b) S. solodovnikovi, c) S. kahurangiensis, d) S. bullerensis, e) S. canterburyensis. Aedeagi, dorsal views: f) S. socia, g) S. solodovnikovi, h) S. kahurangiensis, i) S. bullerensis, j) S. canterburyensis. k) S. socia, dorsal surface of male head. Scale bars a–e = 1 mm, f–k = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907863/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 47h</figureCitation>
). Parameres symmetrical with setae apically to middle (
<figureCitation box="[451,537,991,1012]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[175,207,1148,1167]" captionTargetBox="[162,1162,196,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-275@83.[151,1171,183,1124]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 47. Sagola species in the socia species-group. Habitus, dorsal views: a) S. socia, b) S. solodovnikovi, c) S. kahurangiensis, d) S. bullerensis, e) S. canterburyensis. Aedeagi, dorsal views: f) S. socia, g) S. solodovnikovi, h) S. kahurangiensis, i) S. bullerensis, j) S. canterburyensis. k) S. socia, dorsal surface of male head. Scale bars a–e = 1 mm, f–k = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907863/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 47h</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
